{"title":"*Conclave*","link":"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/906974588/0/marginalrevolution~Conclave.html","date":1730059784000,"content":"<p>I would say this was a good not great movie, but I pass along word because it is rare to have a movie so exclusively devoted to both public choice and social choice theory, and realistically so.  (Thomas Reese said in an interview that the details on the conclave were pretty realistic too; if you don’t know of Reese his book <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://www.amazon.com/Inside-Vatican-Politics-Organization-Catholic-ebook/dp/B0BSLBXPNH/ref=sr_1_1?crid=2TW7T8ZHRDS37&amp;dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9.o6HDx2JCJtQiW_2IWmCDYQskP3CzFg_9LN24zHb5-2Y.W9IUgYUi359ep-utFnfsJCBIqRIyCX7fR1yCJOrkg4w&amp;dib_tag=se&amp;keywords=thomas+reese+inside+the+vatican&amp;qid=1730059576&amp;sprefix=thomas+reese+inside%2Caps%2C113&amp;sr=8-1\" target=\"_blank\">Inside the Vatican</a> is perhaps the best book on bureaucracy ever.)</p>\r\n<p>I cannot say much more without spoiling the plot.  Needless to say, Richard McKelvey would not have walked away from this one feeling refuted…</p>\r\n<p>The film also takes itself seriously in a good way, which these days in Hollywood is increasingly rare.</p>\r\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://marginalrevolution.com/marginalrevolution/2024/10/conclave.html\">*Conclave*</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://marginalrevolution.com\">Marginal REVOLUTION</a>.</p>\r\n<img height=\"1\" width=\"1\" src=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/i/906974588/0/marginalrevolution\" />\r\n<div><a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/_/28/906974588/marginalrevolution\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"https://assets.feedblitz.com/i/fblike20.png\" /></a> <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/_/29/906974588/marginalrevolution,\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"https://assets.feedblitz.com/i/pinterest20.png\" /></a> <a h